A businesswoman from Embu is the winner of a brand-new Isuzu NMR Truck, valued at Sh4 million in the ongoing promotion by Vivo Energy and Isuzu East Africa. The National Consumer Campaign running for 12 weeks has seen consumers of Shell lubricants win daily, weekly and monthly prizes. Every customer buying Shell Fuels or Shell Lubricants receives a scratch card to enter the promotion that has been running since November 12 last year. To be eligible for the promotion, motorcyclists are required to spend a minimum of Sh300, while vehicles are required to spend a minimum of Sh1000. "I take this opportunity to congratulate Wincate Wawira Mwaniki for being the lucky winner of this powerful vehicle.Â It will go a long way in improving and enhancing her business." Vivo Energy managing director Peter Murungi said. He added that the promotion is a way of giving back to their customers and boosting their business plans and income. Murungi urged customers to continue participating in the campaign as they stand a chance to win the grand prize of a three-bedroomed house. The businesswoman plans to use the truck to venture into farm produce transportation. Rose Mombo, sales manager at Isuzu East Africa, thanked Vivo Energy for according them an opportunity as their logistical provider.